      "lineNbr": 35,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000042
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-14T00:22:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "hmm. if i\u0027m understanding the RFC correctly, direct-tcpip actually accepts either a hostname or an IP address: https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4254#section-7.2\n\nit\u0027s not obvious to me why ssh.Client.DialTCP takes a net.TCPAddr (which i think can only hold an IP address): https://godoc.org/golang.org/x/crypto/ssh#Client.DialTCP\n\nthere\u0027s also ssh.Client.Dial, which looks like it passes the remote hostname directly, but always uses net.IPv4zero.String() and port 0 locally. we could switch to that, but i don\u0027t know if there are security concerns around listening on 0.0.0.0 instead of localhost.",
      "parentUuid": "7d8d6cce_fdff8245",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 57,
        "endLine": 35,
        "endChar": 57
      },
      "revId": "2985495c1b4b16f35570162a62725eb1f130e397",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
